Campus Recruitment¶

Academic and Employability Factors influencing placement¶



Hello¶

My name is Ben Roshan D, doing MBA in Business Analytics at Jain University Bangalore . We have practical sessions in Python,R as subjects. Faculties provide us with such data sets to work on with it, So here is one of the data set which our class worked on

What is in it?¶

This data set consists of Placement data of students in a XYZ campus. It includes secondary and higher secondary school percentage and specialization. It also includes degree specialization, type and Work experience and salary offers to the placed students

使用FMI评分确定类别数

In [18]:



     


from sklearn.metrics import fowlkes_mallows_score
for i in range(2,7):
    kmeans=KMeans(n_clusters=i,random_state=123).fit(x_trainPCA)
    score1=fowlkes_mallows_score(y_train,kmeans.labels_)
    print('{}FMI{}'.format(i,score1))

使用随机森林——训练集与验证集
¶










In [36]:



     


from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
superpa = []
for i in range(100):
    rfc = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=i+1,n_jobs=-1)
    rfc_s = cross_val_score(rfc,x_trainPCA,y_train,cv=10).mean()
    superpa.append(rfc_s)
print('{:.2f}{}'.format(max(superpa),superpa.index(max(superpa))))
plt.figure(figsize=[20,5])
plt.plot(range(1,101),superpa)
plt.show()



     


















    
    






0.8878

在模型中，哪个变量更重要？
¶










In [57]:



     


from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
rfc = RandomForestClassifier().fit(x_train,y_train)
features_list = x_train.columns.values
feature_importance = rfc.feature_importances_
sorted_idx = np.argsort(feature_importance)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.barh(range(len(sorted_idx)), feature_importance[sorted_idx], align='center')
plt.yticks(range(len(sorted_idx)), features_list[sorted_idx])
plt.xlabel('Importance')
plt.title('Feature importances')
plt.draw()
plt.show()

In [68]:



     


from sklearn.svm import SVC
svm_data=SVC().fit(x_trainPCA,y_train)
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
accuracies = cross_val_score(estimator = svm_data, X = x_train, y = y_train, cv = 10)
print(": {:.2f} %".format(accuracies.mean()*100))
print(": {:.2f} %".format(accuracies.std()*100))

print('{:.2f},gamma={:.2f}'.format(max(score), gamma_range[score.index(max(score))]))
print('{:.2f},gamma={:.2f}'.format(max(score_test), gamma_range[score_test.index(max(score_test))]))
plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
plt.plot(gamma_range,score,color='orange')
plt.xlabel('gamma')
plt.plot(gamma_range,score_test,color='c')
plt.legend(['train','test'])
plt.show()

ROC曲线与AUC值
¶










AUCROCAUC











绘制ROC曲线
¶










In [105]:



     


from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
fpr1,tpr1,thresholds1=roc_curve(y_test_label,y_predict_label_rfc)
fpr2,tpr2,threshold2=roc_curve(y_test_label,y_predict_label_svm)
plt.xlim(0,1)
plt.ylim(0.0,1.1)
plt.xlabel("False Postive Rate")
plt.ylabel("True Postive Rate")
plt.plot(fpr1,tpr1,linestyle='-',color='pink',)
plt.plot(fpr2,tpr2,linestyle='-',color='c')
plt.legend(['Random Forest','SVM'],)
plt.show()

In [102]:



     


from sklearn import metrics
print('AUC{:.2f}'.format(metrics.auc(fpr1, tpr1)))
print('SVMAUC{:.2f}'.format(metrics.auc(fpr2, tpr2)))
